_dc:description: Other known identifier used for the same taxon. Can be a URL pointing to a webpage, an xml or rdf document, a DOI, UUID or any other identifer
An optional display label for the URL that the publisher may prefer be displayed with the identifier or link

mime type of content returned by identifier in case the identifier is resolvable. Plain UUIDs for example do not have a dc:format return type, as they are not resolvable on their own. For a list of MIME types see the list maintained by IANA: http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/index.html, in particular the text http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/text/ and application http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/application/ types. Frequently used values are text/html, text/xml, application/rdf+xml, application/json
An identifier for a subset of data.
